As a military parent who has served on the Armed Services Committee, I have the utmost respect for the risks taken by those who work every day to protect our national security, which includes those in our intelligence community. I am deeply disturbed by Donald Trump’s refusal to take seriously the conclusions reached by the intelligence community regarding Russian influence in our electoral system and engagement in cyber-attacks against American citizens. It is imperative that after his intelligence briefing tomorrow, Donald Trump change his tone and show those who risk their lives for American citizens the respect they deserve.

I introduced legislation today that would hold members of congress accountable during the debate over healthcare coverage. When Members of Congress vote on legislation that could lead to an increase in the nation’s uninsured rate, they must be able to live by the same rules they are forcing on the American people.   The "Holding Congress Accountable on Healthcare Act" is simple; if legislation that makes changes to the ACA is signed into law and the uninsured rate goes up, then Members of Congress lose their healthcare coverage, which is provided through the ACA exchanges. I truly believe Members of Congress must have a personal stake in the future of our nation’s healthcare policy.

No matter what happens with the debate over healthcare, Members of Congress must be held accountable for their actions, they have to have some skin in the game. That is why I introduced the Holding Congress Accountable on Healthcare Act. The bottom line is, if legislation that makes changes to the ACA is signed into law and the uninsured rate goes up, then Members of Congress should lose their healthcare coverage.

Yesterday, the Federal Communications Commission voted to repeal net neutrality provisions and I want to know how you feel.  I am committed to ensuring that content on the internet is prevented from being blocked, that Internet 'fast lanes' are not instituted, that greater transparency is provided to users and that content cannot be 'throttled' or slowed down based on whether the content is affiliated with any particular Internet service provider.
